  "text": "The scale of the infiltrations can perhaps be gauged by examining the proportions of genetic admixture in Khoisan populations. To provide a basis for comparison, it is worth noting that the Bantu migrations, which are clearly evident in the archaeological record are also strongly recorded in the genetic data. In south-western Angola, among some of the most admixed Bantu-speaking populations of southern Africa, the patterns of lineage sharing and admixture estimates suggest that around 75% of mtDNA variation can be traced back to West-Central Africa, which indicates a significant population migration and not a minor infiltration [CITATION_1] . In general, the maternal genepool of the Bantu-speaking populations of southern Africa is very homogenous [CITATION_2] , again indicating that a coherent and large population was involved in the migration that brought them into southern Africa.",
